article.headline: Clemson 77, Dayton 69
article.story:
CLEMSON, S.C. (AP) -- D'Lesha Lloyd posted her fourth double-double of the season with 25 points and 13 rebounds in leading Clemson to a 77-69 victory over Dayton on Tuesday night.

Lady Tigers Adrianne Bradshaw and Lele Hardy also scored in double figures, while Tasha Taylor recorded a team-high five assists.

Nikki Oakland led Dayton with 29 points, and her nine rebounds tied for a game-high with teammate Brittany Holterman.

Clemson (6-6) jumped out to a 28-16 lead in the game's first eight minutes, but Dayton (4-7) held the Lady Tigers to just 7 points the rest of the period.

The Flyers tied the game at 30 at 4:31 on a jumper by Oakland, who went on to give her team the lead with 1:28 remaining in the half. Dayton led 36-35 at halftime.

Clemson took back the lead just seven seconds into the second half and never relinquished the lead. The Lady Tigers led by as many as 14 points at the 11:29 mark, as a jumper by Lloyd put them on top 57-43.

The Flyers outscored Clemson, 8-3, in the final minutes.
